{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":761,"text":"What has the War on Drugs \ndone to the world?"},{"time":4975,"text":"Look at the murder and mayhem in Mexico,"},{"time":7152,"text":"Central America, so many \nother parts of the planet,"},{"time":10999,"text":"the global black market estimated"},{"time":12799,"text":"at 300 billion dollars a year,"},{"time":15375,"text":"prisons packed in the \nUnited States and elsewhere,"},{"time":18817,"text":"police and military drawn \ninto an unwinnable war"},{"time":21495,"text":"that violates basic rights, \nand ordinary citizens"},{"time":24757,"text":"just hope they don't get \ncaught in the crossfire,"},{"time":27738,"text":"and meanwhile, more people using"},{"time":30100,"text":"more drugs than ever."},{"time":32361,"text":"It's my country's history \nwith alcohol prohibition"},{"time":34656,"text":"and Al Capone, times 50."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37783,"text":"Which is why it's \nparticularly galling to me"},{"time":41336,"text":"as an American that we've \nbeen the driving force"},{"time":44465,"text":"behind this global drug war."},{"time":46501,"text":"Ask why so many countries criminalize"},{"time":48503,"text":"drugs they'd never heard of,"},{"time":50292,"text":"why the U.N. drug treaties emphasize"},{"time":53318,"text":"criminalization over health,"},{"time":55540,"text":"even why most of the money worldwide"},{"time":57884,"text":"for dealing with drug abuse goes not"},{"time":59549,"text":"to helping agencies but those that punish,"},{"time":62320,"text":"and you'll find the good old U.S. of A."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65639,"text":"Why did we do this?"},{"time":67817,"text":"Some people, especially in Latin America,"},{"time":71113,"text":"think it's not really about drugs."},{"time":72846,"text":"It's just a subterfuge for advancing"},{"time":75009,"text":"the realpolitik interests of the U.S."},{"time":78167,"text":"But by and large, that's not it."},{"time":81530,"text":"We don't want gangsters and guerrillas"},{"time":84443,"text":"funded with illegal drug money"},{"time":86513,"text":"terrorizing and taking over other nations."},{"time":89629,"text":"No, the fact is, America really is crazy"},{"time":94200,"text":"when it comes to drugs."},{"time":96040,"text":"I mean, don't forget, we're \nthe ones who thought"},{"time":98200,"text":"that we could prohibit alcohol."},{"time":99866,"text":"So think about our global drug war"},{"time":102149,"text":"not as any sort of rational policy,"},{"time":104885,"text":"but as the international projection"},{"time":107627,"text":"of a domestic psychosis."},{"time":111114,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":114160,"text":"But here's the good news."},{"time":115827,"text":"Now it's the Russians leading\nthe Drug War and not us."},{"time":119120,"text":"Most politicians in my country"},{"time":120700,"text":"want to roll back the Drug War now,"},{"time":122021,"text":"put fewer people behind bars, not more,"},{"time":124833,"text":"and I'm proud to say as an American"},{"time":127342,"text":"that we now lead the world"},{"time":128926,"text":"in reforming marijuana policies."},{"time":131166,"text":"It's now legal for medical purposes"},{"time":133112,"text":"in almost half our 50 states,"},{"time":134912,"text":"millions of people can \npurchase their marijuana,"},{"time":137274,"text":"their medicine, in government-\nlicensed dispensaries,"},{"time":140190,"text":"and over half my fellow \ncitizens now say it's time"},{"time":143270,"text":"to legally regulate and tax marijuana"},{"time":145643,"text":"more or less like alcohol."},{"time":147320,"text":"That's what Colorado and \nWashington are doing,"},{"time":149287,"text":"and Uruguay, and others \nare sure to follow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153673,"text":"So that's what I do:"},{"time":156161,"text":"work to end the Drug War."},{"time":159967,"text":"I think it all started growing up"},{"time":162626,"text":"in a fairly religious, moral family,"},{"time":165205,"text":"eldest son of a rabbi,"},{"time":167241,"text":"going off to university where I"},{"time":169412,"text":"smoked some marijuana"},{"time":172762,"text":"and I liked it. (Laughter)"},{"time":174980,"text":"And I liked drinking too, but it was obvious"},{"time":177455,"text":"that alcohol was really the\nmore dangerous of the two,"},{"time":179930,"text":"but my friends and I could get busted"},{"time":181617,"text":"for smoking a joint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183190,"text":"Now, that hypocrisy kept bugging me,"},{"time":185749,"text":"so I wrote my Ph.D dissertation\non international drug control."},{"time":188690,"text":"I talked my way into the State Department."},{"time":191180,"text":"I got a security clearance."},{"time":192409,"text":"I interviewed hundreds of DEA\nand other law enforcement agents"},{"time":195373,"text":"all around Europe and the Americas,"},{"time":197530,"text":"and I'd ask them,"},{"time":198761,"text":"\"What do you think the answer is?\""},{"time":201385,"text":"Well, in Latin America, they'd say to me,"},{"time":204165,"text":"\"You can't really cut off the supply."},{"time":206980,"text":"The answer lies back in the U.S.,"},{"time":208534,"text":"in cutting off the demand.\""},{"time":210337,"text":"So then I go back home and I talk to people"},{"time":212853,"text":"involved in anti-drug efforts there, and they'd say,"},{"time":215453,"text":"\"You know, Ethan, you can't \nreally cut off the demand."},{"time":218681,"text":"The answer lies over there.\nYou've got to cut off the supply.\""},{"time":221628,"text":"Then I'd go and talk \nto the guys in customs"},{"time":224238,"text":"trying to stop drugs at the borders,"},{"time":226600,"text":"and they'd say, \"You're \nnot going to stop it here."},{"time":229817,"text":"The answer lies over there,"},{"time":231786,"text":"in cutting off supply and demand.\""},{"time":234778,"text":"And it hit me:"},{"time":236408,"text":"Everybody involved in this"},{"time":238693,"text":"thought the answer lay in that area"},{"time":241133,"text":"about which they knew the least."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244141,"text":"So that's when I started \nreading everything I could"},{"time":246645,"text":"about psychoactive drugs: \nthe history, the science,"},{"time":249525,"text":"the politics, all of it,"},{"time":251630,"text":"and the more one read,"},{"time":253946,"text":"the more it hit you how a thoughtful,"},{"time":256488,"text":"enlightened, intelligent \napproach took you over here,"},{"time":259852,"text":"whereas the politics and laws of my country"},{"time":262360,"text":"were taking you over here."},{"time":264396,"text":"And that disparity struck me as this incredible"},{"time":268187,"text":"intellectual and moral puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274385,"text":"There's probably never been"},{"time":276411,"text":"a drug-free society."},{"time":279020,"text":"Virtually every society"},{"time":280770,"text":"has ingested psychoactive substances"},{"time":283171,"text":"to deal with pain, increase \nour energy, socialize,"},{"time":286786,"text":"even commune with God."},{"time":288819,"text":"Our desire to alter our consciousness"},{"time":291507,"text":"may be as fundamental as our desires"},{"time":293937,"text":"for food, companionship and sex."},{"time":297854,"text":"So our true challenge"},{"time":299991,"text":"is to learn how to live with drugs"},{"time":302871,"text":"so they cause the least possible harm"},{"time":305627,"text":"and in some cases the \ngreatest possible benefit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309840,"text":"I'll tell you something else I learned,"},{"time":311910,"text":"that the reason some drugs \nare legal and others not"},{"time":314998,"text":"has almost nothing to do \nwith science or health"},{"time":317956,"text":"or the relative risk of drugs,"},{"time":319789,"text":"and almost everything to do with who uses"},{"time":322185,"text":"and who is perceived \nto use particular drugs."},{"time":325313,"text":"In the late 19th century,"},{"time":327383,"text":"when most of the drugs that\nare now illegal were legal,"},{"time":330723,"text":"the principal consumers \nof opiates in my country"},{"time":333435,"text":"and others were middle-aged white women,"},{"time":337239,"text":"using them to alleviate aches and pains"},{"time":339598,"text":"when few other analgesics were available."},{"time":342320,"text":"And nobody thought about \ncriminalizing it back then"},{"time":344481,"text":"because nobody wanted to \nput Grandma behind bars."},{"time":347478,"text":"But when hundreds of thousands of Chinese"},{"time":349936,"text":"started showing up in my country,"},{"time":351725,"text":"working hard on the railroads and the mines"},{"time":354323,"text":"and then kicking back in the evening"},{"time":355802,"text":"just like they had in the old country"},{"time":357506,"text":"with a few puffs on that opium pipe,"},{"time":360163,"text":"that's when you saw the \nfirst drug prohibition laws"},{"time":362480,"text":"in California and Nevada,"},{"time":364280,"text":"driven by racist fears of Chinese"},{"time":366158,"text":"transforming white women"},{"time":367994,"text":"into opium-addicted sex slaves."},{"time":371378,"text":"The first cocaine prohibition \nlaws, similarly prompted"},{"time":374213,"text":"by racist fears of black men \nsniffing that white powder"},{"time":377980,"text":"and forgetting their proper place"},{"time":379859,"text":"in Southern society."},{"time":381813,"text":"And the first marijuana prohibition laws,"},{"time":383796,"text":"all about fears of Mexican migrants"},{"time":385869,"text":"in the West and the Southwest."},{"time":389645,"text":"And what was true in my country,"},{"time":392379,"text":"is true in so many others as well,"},{"time":394876,"text":"with both the origins of these laws"},{"time":397120,"text":"and their implementation."},{"time":400543,"text":"Put it this way,"},{"time":402160,"text":"and I exaggerate only slightly:"},{"time":404841,"text":"If the principal smokers of cocaine"},{"time":407923,"text":"were affluent older white men"},{"time":409917,"text":"and the principal consumers of Viagra"},{"time":412906,"text":"were poor young black men,"},{"time":414800,"text":"then smokable cocaine would be easy to\nget with a prescription from your doctor"},{"time":417912,"text":"and selling Viagra would get you \nfive to 10 years behind bars."},{"time":421197,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424981,"text":"I used to be a professor teaching about this."},{"time":428835,"text":"Now I'm an activist, a human rights activist,"},{"time":432490,"text":"and what drives me is my shame"},{"time":435251,"text":"at living in an otherwise great nation"},{"time":437429,"text":"that has less than five percent\nof the world's population"},{"time":440212,"text":"but almost 25 percent of the\nworld's incarcerated population."},{"time":443840,"text":"It's the people I meet \nwho have lost someone"},{"time":446241,"text":"they love to drug-related \nviolence or prison"},{"time":448795,"text":"or overdose or AIDS"},{"time":450257,"text":"because our drug policies emphasize"},{"time":452237,"text":"criminalization over health."},{"time":454261,"text":"It's good people who have lost their jobs,"},{"time":457490,"text":"their homes, their freedom, \neven their children"},{"time":461120,"text":"to the state, not because they hurt anyone"},{"time":464588,"text":"but solely because they chose to use one drug"},{"time":467813,"text":"instead of another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470827,"text":"So is legalization the answer?"},{"time":475176,"text":"On that, I'm torn:"},{"time":477213,"text":"three days a week I think yes,\nthree days a week I think no,"},{"time":480396,"text":"and on Sundays I'm agnostic."},{"time":482616,"text":"But since today is Tuesday,"},{"time":485142,"text":"let me just say that legally \nregulating and taxing"},{"time":489844,"text":"most of the drugs that \nare now criminalized"},{"time":492262,"text":"would radically reduce \nthe crime, violence,"},{"time":494636,"text":"corruption and black markets,"},{"time":496368,"text":"and the problems of adulterated\nand unregulated drugs,"},{"time":499405,"text":"and improve public safety,"},{"time":501352,"text":"and allow taxpayer resources to be developed"},{"time":503556,"text":"to more useful purposes."},{"time":505772,"text":"I mean, look, the markets \nin marijuana, cocaine,"},{"time":509552,"text":"heroin and methamphetamine"},{"time":511565,"text":"are global commodities markets"},{"time":514130,"text":"just like the global markets \nin alcohol, tobacco,"},{"time":517325,"text":"coffee, sugar, and so many other things."},{"time":520205,"text":"Where there is a demand,"},{"time":522601,"text":"there will be a supply."},{"time":525124,"text":"Knock out one source and another"},{"time":527280,"text":"inevitably emerges."},{"time":528990,"text":"People tend to think of prohibition"},{"time":531370,"text":"as the ultimate form of regulation"},{"time":533868,"text":"when in fact it represents \nthe abdication of regulation"},{"time":537887,"text":"with criminals filling the void."},{"time":541904,"text":"Which is why putting criminal laws and police"},{"time":544164,"text":"front and center in trying to control"},{"time":547382,"text":"a dynamic global commodities market"},{"time":550486,"text":"is a recipe for disaster."},{"time":553355,"text":"And what we really need to do"},{"time":555526,"text":"is to bring the underground drug markets"},{"time":557900,"text":"as much as possible aboveground"},{"time":560813,"text":"and regulate them as \nintelligently as we can"},{"time":564885,"text":"to minimize both the harms of drugs"},{"time":567674,"text":"and the harms of prohibitionist policies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571162,"text":"Now, with marijuana, that obviously means"},{"time":574727,"text":"legally regulating and \ntaxing it like alcohol."},{"time":577393,"text":"The benefits of doing so are\nenormous, the risks minimal."},{"time":580723,"text":"Will more people use marijuana?"},{"time":583434,"text":"Maybe, but it's not \ngoing to be young people,"},{"time":587405,"text":"because it's not going to \nbe legalized for them,"},{"time":589407,"text":"and quite frankly, they already have"},{"time":591218,"text":"the best access to marijuana."},{"time":593254,"text":"I think it's going to be older people."},{"time":595403,"text":"It's going to be people in their 40s and 60s"},{"time":597562,"text":"and 80s who find they prefer a little marijuana"},{"time":601208,"text":"to that drink in the evening or the sleeping pill"},{"time":604498,"text":"or that it helps with \ntheir arthritis or diabetes"},{"time":608138,"text":"or maybe helps spice up a \nlong-term marriage. (Laughter)"},{"time":613330,"text":"And that just might be a \nnet public health benefit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616484,"text":"As for the other drugs,"},{"time":618846,"text":"look at Portugal, where \nnobody goes to jail"},{"time":621467,"text":"for possessing drugs,"},{"time":623230,"text":"and the government's made \na serious commitment"},{"time":624600,"text":"to treating addiction as a health issue."},{"time":626810,"text":"Look at Switzerland, \nGermany, the Netherlands,"},{"time":628711,"text":"Denmark, England, where people who have"},{"time":630657,"text":"been addicted to heroin for many years"},{"time":632558,"text":"and repeatedly tried to quit and failed"},{"time":634864,"text":"can get pharmaceutical \nheroin and helping services"},{"time":637722,"text":"in medical clinics, and \nthe results are in:"},{"time":641163,"text":"Illegal drug abuse and disease"},{"time":644227,"text":"and overdoses and crime \nand arrests all go down,"},{"time":648374,"text":"health and well-being improve,"},{"time":650523,"text":"taxpayers benefit,"},{"time":652255,"text":"and many drug users even\nput their addictions behind them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656405,"text":"Look at New Zealand, which \nrecently enacted a law"},{"time":659207,"text":"allowing certain recreational \ndrugs to be sold legally"},{"time":662142,"text":"provided their safety had been established."},{"time":664843,"text":"Look here in Brazil, and some other countries,"},{"time":667542,"text":"where a remarkable psychoactive substance,"},{"time":670605,"text":"ayahuasca, can be legally \nbought and consumed"},{"time":673830,"text":"provided it's done so \nwithin a religious context."},{"time":676958,"text":"Look in Bolivia and Peru,"},{"time":678960,"text":"where all sorts of products \nmade from the coca leaf,"},{"time":681749,"text":"the source of cocaine,"},{"time":683650,"text":"are sold legally over the counter"},{"time":685270,"text":"with no apparent harm to people's public health."},{"time":688403,"text":"I mean, don't forget, Coca-Cola\nhad cocaine in it until 1900,"},{"time":692439,"text":"and so far as we know was no more addictive"},{"time":694407,"text":"than Coca-Cola is today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698460,"text":"Conversely, think about cigarettes:"},{"time":701537,"text":"Nothing can both hook you \nand kill you like cigarettes."},{"time":706523,"text":"When researchers ask heroin addicts"},{"time":709587,"text":"what's the toughest drug to \nquit, most say cigarettes."},{"time":712793,"text":"Yet in my country and many others,"},{"time":715167,"text":"half of all the people who \nwere ever addicted"},{"time":717709,"text":"to cigarettes have quit"},{"time":719644,"text":"without anyone being \narrested or put in jail"},{"time":722652,"text":"or sent to a \"treatment program\""},{"time":724908,"text":"by a prosecutor or a judge."},{"time":726641,"text":"What did it were higher taxes"},{"time":729937,"text":"and time and place \nrestrictions on sale and use"},{"time":733480,"text":"and effective anti-smoking campaigns."},{"time":736552,"text":"Now, could we reduce smoking even more"},{"time":740492,"text":"by making it totally illegal? Probably."},{"time":744831,"text":"But just imagine the drug war nightmare"},{"time":748442,"text":"that would result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":751480,"text":"So the challenges we face today"},{"time":753763,"text":"are twofold."},{"time":755630,"text":"The first is the policy challenge"},{"time":758645,"text":"of designing and implementing alternatives"},{"time":762323,"text":"to ineffective prohibitionist policies,"},{"time":764741,"text":"even as we need to get \nbetter at regulating"},{"time":768161,"text":"and living with the drugs \nthat are now legal."},{"time":771830,"text":"But the second challenge is tougher,"},{"time":775191,"text":"because it's about us."},{"time":778802,"text":"The obstacles to reform \nlie not just out there"},{"time":782290,"text":"in the power of the \nprison industrial complex"},{"time":784450,"text":"or other vested interests \nthat want to keep things"},{"time":786654,"text":"the way they are,"},{"time":788080,"text":"but within each and every one of us."},{"time":791920,"text":"It's our fears and our lack of knowledge"},{"time":795970,"text":"and imagination that stands \nin the way of real reform."},{"time":802670,"text":"And ultimately, I think that \nboils down to the kids,"},{"time":807240,"text":"and to every parent's desire\nto put our baby in a bubble,"},{"time":810985,"text":"and the fear that somehow\ndrugs will pierce that bubble"},{"time":814315,"text":"and put our young ones at risk."},{"time":816244,"text":"In fact, sometimes it \nseems like the entire"},{"time":818314,"text":"War on Drugs gets justified"},{"time":820290,"text":"as one great big child protection act,"},{"time":824216,"text":"which any young person \ncan tell you it's not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827823,"text":"So here's what I say to teenagers."},{"time":831929,"text":"First, don't do drugs."},{"time":835615,"text":"Second, don't do drugs."},{"time":839405,"text":"Third, if you do do drugs,"},{"time":842825,"text":"there's some things I want you to know,"},{"time":845367,"text":"because my bottom line as your parent is,"},{"time":849410,"text":"come home safely at the end of the night"},{"time":852391,"text":"and grow up and lead a \nhealthy and good adulthood."},{"time":855924,"text":"That's my drug education \nmantra: Safety first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861537,"text":"So this is what I've dedicated my life to,"},{"time":865193,"text":"to building an organization and a movement"},{"time":867701,"text":"of people who believe we \nneed to turn our backs"},{"time":870561,"text":"on the failed prohibitions of the past"},{"time":872606,"text":"and embrace new drug \npolicies grounded in science,"},{"time":875305,"text":"compassion, health and human rights,"},{"time":878246,"text":"where people who come from\nacross the political spectrum"},{"time":880884,"text":"and every other spectrum as well,"},{"time":882865,"text":"where people who love our drugs,"},{"time":884599,"text":"people who hate drugs,"},{"time":885938,"text":"and people who don't give \na damn about drugs,"},{"time":888250,"text":"but every one of us believes \nthat this War on Drugs,"},{"time":891684,"text":"this backward, heartless, \ndisastrous War on Drugs,"},{"time":895931,"text":"has got to end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899030,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":900873,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":915042,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917722,"text":"Chris Anderson: Ethan,"},{"time":919943,"text":"congrats — quite the reaction."},{"time":923182,"text":"That was a powerful talk."},{"time":925926,"text":"Not quite a complete standing O, though,"},{"time":929234,"text":"and I'm guessing that some people here"},{"time":930921,"text":"and maybe a few watching online,"},{"time":933187,"text":"maybe someone knows a teenager or a friend"},{"time":937287,"text":"or whatever who got sick,"},{"time":939504,"text":"maybe died from some drug overdose."},{"time":942500,"text":"I'm sure you've had these\npeople approach you before."},{"time":944386,"text":"What do you say to them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":946557,"text":"Ethan Nadelmann: Chris, the most\namazing thing that's happened of late"},{"time":948739,"text":"is that I've met a growing number of people"},{"time":950980,"text":"who have actually \nlost a sibling or a child"},{"time":953558,"text":"to a drug overdose,"},{"time":955184,"text":"and 10 years ago, those \npeople just wanted to say,"},{"time":957160,"text":"let's line up all the drug \ndealers and shoot them"},{"time":959140,"text":"and that will solve it."},{"time":960481,"text":"And what they've come to understand"},{"time":961776,"text":"is that the Drug War did \nnothing to protect their kids."},{"time":964659,"text":"If anything, it made it more likely"},{"time":966108,"text":"that those kids were put at risk."},{"time":968210,"text":"And so they're now becoming part of this"},{"time":969820,"text":"drug policy reform movement."},{"time":971695,"text":"There's other people who have kids,"},{"time":973385,"text":"one's addicted to alcohol, the other\none's addicted to cocaine or heroin,"},{"time":976850,"text":"and they ask themselves the question:"},{"time":978278,"text":"Why does this kid get to \ntake one step at a time"},{"time":980595,"text":"and try to get better"},{"time":981889,"text":"and that one's got to deal with jail"},{"time":983453,"text":"and police and criminals all the time?"},{"time":985478,"text":"So everybody's understanding,"},{"time":986948,"text":"the Drug War's not protecting anybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989673,"text":"CA: Certainly in the U.S., \nyou've got political gridlock"},{"time":991754,"text":"on most issues."},{"time":993149,"text":"Is there any realistic chance of anything"},{"time":994881,"text":"actually shifting on this \nissue in the next five years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":998227,"text":"EN: I'd say it's quite remarkable. \nI'm getting all these calls"},{"time":1000245,"text":"from journalists now who are saying to me,"},{"time":1002126,"text":"\"Ethan, it seems like the only two issues"},{"time":1004130,"text":"advancing politically in America right now"},{"time":1006423,"text":"are marijuana law reform and gay marriage."},{"time":1009314,"text":"What are you doing right?\""},{"time":1010891,"text":"And then you're looking at \nbipartisanship breaking out"},{"time":1013479,"text":"with, actually, Republicans in the Congress"},{"time":1015771,"text":"and state legislatures \nallowing bills to be enacted"},{"time":1018840,"text":"with majority Democratic support,"},{"time":1020804,"text":"so we've gone from being sort of the third rail,"},{"time":1023320,"text":"the most fearful issue of American politics,"},{"time":1025411,"text":"to becoming one of the most successful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028161,"text":"CA: Ethan, thank you so much for coming to TEDGlobal.\nEN: Chris, thanks so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030344,"text":"CA: Thank you.\nEN: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}